# SCSS with BEM

## Naming

- Use BEM: `.block__element--modifier`. Block = standalone component, element = part of it, modifier = variant or state.
- No deep nesting beyond 2 levels. Elements do not nest inside elements (`.block__elem1__elem2` is wrong — flatten it).
- No `#id` selectors. No `!important`. No inline styles.

## Nesting (allowed cases only)

Use SCSS `&` nesting only for:
- Pseudo-classes: `&:hover`, `&:focus`, `&:focus-visible`
- Pseudo-elements: `&::before`, `&::after`
- Modifiers: `&--active`, `&--disabled`
- Media queries: `@media (min-width: ...)`

Never nest a child block inside a parent block's rule. Each block owns its own top-level rule.

```scss
// Good
.card { ... }
.card__title { ... }
.card__title--large { ... }
.card:hover { ... }

// Bad — nested child block
.card {
  .button { ... }   // wrong: button is its own block
}
```

## Design tokens

- Define all design values as CSS custom properties in `:root`: colors, spacing, radii, font sizes, shadows.
- Never hardcode hex values, pixel sizes, or font stacks inline — always reference a token.

```scss
// Good
color: var(--color-text-primary);
padding: var(--spacing-4);

// Bad
color: #1a1a2e;
padding: 16px;
```

## File organisation

- One partial per component: `_card.scss`, `_modal.scss`.
- Use `@use` not `@import`.
- Tokens/variables go in `_tokens.scss` or `_variables.scss`, imported first.

## Media queries — mobile-first

- Base styles target mobile. Desktop overrides go in `@media (min-width: ...)`.
- Media queries live inside the block rule they affect, not in a separate file.

```scss
.card {
  padding: var(--spacing-3);

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    padding: var(--spacing-6);
  }
}
```

## Modifiers

Modifiers only override a property or two — never redefine the full block.

```scss
// Good
.btn--large { font-size: var(--text-lg); padding: var(--spacing-4) var(--spacing-6); }

// Bad
.btn--large { /* copy-paste of entire .btn with one change */ }
```
